text.0: The latest on Q from @TheOndrakGuy, me, and the @LogicallyAI team. https://t.co/kWLFhqRbdD

text.6: Since our previous investigation outing Jason Gelinas, former info sec specialist at CitiGroup, as the operator of QMap, VanwaTech has been adding more and more Q-drop aggregators to its servers, giving the company an enormous amount of control over QAnon communications.
text.7: Logically has also found that Lim, who defends hosting neo-Nazi forums by saying that he will host anything 'so long as it's legal', has been hosting decidedly not legal phishing scams targeted at UK banks and telecoms such as @HSBC_UK, @HalifaxBank, @giffgaff, and @ThreeUK.
text.8: Lots of Q-watchers have speculated about the relationship between VanwaTech owner Nick Lim and 8kun owner Jim Watkins; our investigation is the first to provide solid evidence of such.
text.9:
A Logically Investigation reveals the consolidation of high-level QAnon communications on the hosting company VanwaTech. The company is also hosting phishing scams targeting several UK companies.
